<div class="lexicon-entry">
  <div class="term">Conveyor environment</div>
  <div class="definition">
    <div class="p">
      A Conveyor environment is the primary unit of operation; environments
      provide services; authenication, data, and operations are primarily
      defined in terms of
      environments. Any given <a href="/documentation/conveyor/lexicon/service-request">service
      request</a> is directed at and  handled by a single
      <a href="/documentation/conveyor/lexicon/responsible-environment">responsible
      environment</a>.
    </div>
    <div class="p">
      Authorized users may access Conveyor environments through the
      as <a href="/conveyor-environments"><code>/conveyor-enviroment</code>
      resource</a> from within an active Conveyor enviroment.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
